[3] Switzerland
Date: Mon 16 May 2011
Source: tsrinfo.ch [in French, trans. edited]
http://www.tsr.ch/info/suisse/3145185-l-epidemie-de-rougeole-est-en-forte-hausse-depuis-decembre-geneve-et-vaud-particulierement-touches.html


Since December 2010, 445 cases of measles have been reported in 19
cantons, including 113 cases recorded in March and 187 in April
[2011]. By comparison, there were 59 cases recorded during the 1st 11
months of 2010.

The most severely affected cantons are Basel (62 cases), Geneva (173)
and Vaud (93), where the epidemic has not yet been brought under
control, according to the Federal Office of Public Health. In the
Suisse Romande (French-speaking western Switzerland), measles has
mostly been imported from France, where outbreaks are rampant at the
present time. In eastern Switzerland, there has been a similar
increase in case numbers since April 2011. In Outre-Sarine [central
region], the proportion rose from 10 percent in March to 34 percent in
April 2011.

