[8] Canada (Quebec)
Date: Thu 19 May 2011
Source: cyberpresse.ca [in French, machine trans. abridged, edited]
http://www.cyberpresse.ca/le-nouvelliste/actualites/201105/19/01-4400915-premiers-cas-de-rougeole-a-trois-rivieres.php


2 cases of measles have been reported in Trois-Riviere by the Health
and Social Services Agency [CSSS] of Mauricie and Centre-du-Quebec.
These 2 cases are in addition to 117 others reported by the Health and
Social Services Agency of Drummondville, Arthabaska and l'Erable.

Health Agency records show that the disease continues to spread in
the area served by the Drummondville CSSS. Because measles is highly
contagious among unvaccinated people, 2 approaches have been adopted
to prevent the outbreak spreading. The 1st is to ask the school boards
and health centers to work together to increase immunization coverage
in schools. The same approach will be followed in childcare facilities
by sending reminders and making appointments at health centers.
Similarly, people are being requested to stay at home if they think
they are suffering from measles. "These 2 measures can help to contain
the outbreak, said Dr Lynda Milette of Public Health."

