[11] USA (California)
Wed 18 May 2011
Source: KSBY News, ksby.com [edited]
http://www.ksby.com/news/local-health-officials-confirm-case-of-measles-in-san-luis-obispo-county/


San Luis Obispo County Public Health officials confirmed a case of
measles in a San Luis Obispo county resident who had recently returned
from France. Officials say this is the 1st case of measles in the
county in about 20 years and that there have only been 13 cases of the
virus in California this year [2011]. On the flip side, health
officials say measles has been seen in epidemic levels in France over
the past 2 years.

Public health officials say the local patient returned to the county
in a private car and had not visited any local businesses or public
places, other than a local hospital.

Symptoms of measles include a blotchy, pink or red rash. Patients
with measles can also have a fever, cough, runny nose, red or swollen
watery eyes and white spots in the mouth. Public health officials say,
generally, anyone born before 1957 is immune to measles. Those born
after 1957 and who have received 2 doses of the measles vaccine are
also considered immune.

[Byline: Bethany Tucker]

