[12] USA (California) alert
Date: Sat 21 May 2011
Source: Signon San Diego [edited]
http://www.signonsandiego.com/news/2011/may/21/measles-reported-on-recent-local-flight/


Health authorities on Saturday [21 May 2011] said passengers on a
recent airline flight into San Diego may have been exposed to measles.
The San Diego County Health and Human Services Agency said one person
on the 17 May 2011 trip, Continental Airlines flight 1689, was
hospitalized with an illness confirmed on Friday [20 May 2011] to be
measles.

Officials are contacting passengers with local addresses to warn them
of the exposure and find out whether they have been vaccinated. Those
from outside the region are also being tracked down.

"Measles is highly contagious and is easily spread by coughing,
sneezing or coming in close contact with an infected person," Eric
McDonald, a county deputy public health officer, said in a prepared
statement. "Anyone on the flight should watch for symptoms and contact
their healthcare provider if they show any signs of the disease."
Those concerned about exposure can contact county officials at (858)
565-5255.

[Byline: Steve Schmidt]

