[13] USA (Massachusetts)
Date: Fri 20 May 2011
Source: CBS Boston [edited]
http://boston.cbslocal.com/2011/05/20/2-more-confirmed-cases-of-measles-in-mass/


There are 2 more confirmed cases of the measles in Massachusetts.
Both were discovered this week, bringing the state's total to 15.
According to the Brookline Public Health Department, the 2 cases are
students at Michael Driscoll School in Brookline. The students are
related, but no names or ages have been revealed. The school has
students from kindergarten through 8th grade.

The 2 infected students have a religious exemption for immunizations.
It's not clear yet how they came down with the measles. Both are now
recovering at home.

4 other students at the school also have the religious exemption.
They are not sick. However, they have been sent home for a week as a
precaution.

